channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Reality star Judge Judy says Gen Z are difficult to work with because they got too many trophies
item.description: Judge Judy says pandering parents have set Gen Z up to fail in the corporate rat race.

item.title: Fintech targeted by climate skeptics banks $37 million from likes of UBS, Commerzbank
item.description: Swedish climate fintech Doconomy told CNBC it's raised $36.9 million in a Series B round co-led by the venture arms of UBS and CommerzBank.

item.title: Credit Suisse's last CEO to leave UBS
Florida allows doctors to perform C-sections outside of hospitals
item.description: It is the first state to allow this, siding with a private equity-owned physicians group.

item.title: Thursday's analyst calls: Nvidia price target increase, PayPal gets a big upgrade
item.description: Nvidia and PayPal were among the stocks being talked about by analysts on Thursday.

item.title: Nelson Peltz sells his stake in Disney, weeks after losing proxy fight: report
Jamie Dimon is so over spectators questioning whether his possible move from CEO to chairman would be bad for JPMorgan: 'How the hell do they know? There's no magic to it'
item.description: "The board should do the right thing—if the chairman is getting in the way of the new CEO they should go. If the chairman is helping the new CEO in a million different ways they should stay."

item.title: L’Oreal says it's working on a form of bioprinted skin that can actually ‘feel’
item.description: L'Oreal says it is working with start-ups and research institutions to develop bioprinted skin that can actually "feel."

item.title: $6 for a hot dog? That's what Americans are prepared to spend these days.
Massive ransomware network taken down by ‘Endgame’ international police operation
item.description: Police arrested four “high value” suspects, took down more than 100 servers and seized control of over 2,000 internet domains.

item.title: South Korean tech conglomerate SK Inc. surges 16% after chair's $1 billion divorce settlement
item.description: SK Inc. is one of Korea's largest conglomerates and is the holding firm for SK Hynix, one of the world's biggest memory chip firms.

item.title: Target’s plan to scale back Pride merchandise makes it 'look weak,' expert says
Google promises $2 billion investment in Malaysia as Big Tech splurges on Southeast Asia spending
item.description: Google's pledge follows multi-billion dollar investment pledges from Microsoft and Amazon targeting Southeast Asia.

item.title: BlackRock-backed fintech Trustly says IPO still at least one year out even as profits jump 51%
item.description: Johan Tjarnberg, CEO of Trustly, told CNBC his firm still needs time to prove the value of its open banking tech to investors before going public.

item.title: Faraday Future’s stock plunges, registering largest-ever daily decline
